#. <section class="sutta" id="an5.87"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.87:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.87:0.2"
msgid "9. Theravagga"
msgstr "9. Senior Mendicants"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: sīlasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an5.87:0.3"
msgid "87. Sīlavantasutta"
msgstr "87. Ethical"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.114"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an5.87:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu sabrahmacārīnaṃ piyo "
"ca hoti manāpo ca garu ca bhāvanīyo ca."
msgstr ""
"“A senior mendicant with five qualities is dear and beloved to their "
"spiritual companions, respected and admired."

msgctxt "an5.87:1.2"
msgid "Katamehi pañcahi?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "an5.87:1.3"
msgid ""
"Sīlavā hoti, pātimokkhasaṃvarasaṃvuto viharati. Ācāragocarasampanno "
"aṇumattesu vajjesu bhayadassāvī, samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu;"
msgstr ""
"They’re ethical, restrained in the monastic code, and are accomplished in "
"appropriate behavior and means of collecting alms. Seeing danger in the "
"slightest fault, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken."

#. VAR: sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ → sātthā sabyañjanā (bj)
#. VAR: dhātā → dhatā (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.87:1.4"
msgid ""
"bahussuto hoti sutadharo sutasannicayo, ye te dhammā ādikalyāṇā "
"majjhekalyāṇā pariyosānakalyāṇā sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ "
"parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ abhivadanti, tathārūpāssa dhammā bahussutā honti "
"dhātā vacasā paricitā manasānupekkhitā diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā;"
msgstr ""
"They’re very learned, remembering and keeping what they’ve learned. These "
"teachings are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the "
"end, meaningful and well-phrased, describing a spiritual practice that’s "
"entirely full and pure. They are very learned in such teachings, remembering "
"them, reinforcing them by recitation, mentally scrutinizing them, and "
"comprehending them theoretically."

msgctxt "an5.87:1.5"
msgid ""
"kalyāṇavāco hoti kalyāṇavākkaraṇo poriyā vācāya samannāgato vissaṭṭhāya "
"anelagaḷāya atthassa viññāpaniyā;"
msgstr ""
"They’re a good speaker, with a polished, clear, and articulate voice that "
"expresses the meaning."

msgctxt "an5.87:1.6"
msgid ""
"catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī "
"hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī;"
msgstr ""
"They get the four absorptions—blissful meditations in the present life that "
"belong to the higher mind—when they want, without trouble or difficulty."

msgctxt "an5.87:1.7"
msgid ""
"āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ "
"abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"They realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this "
"very life. And they live having realized it with their own insight due to "
"the ending of defilements."

msgctxt "an5.87:1.8"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu "
"sabrahmacārīnaṃ piyo ca hoti manāpo ca garu ca bhāvanīyo cā”ti."
msgstr ""
"A senior mendicant with these five qualities is dear and beloved to their "
"spiritual companions, respected and admired.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.87:1.9"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
